-- U.S. mortgage applications rise in latest week-MBA
-- By Caroline Valetkevitch
-- Wed Jun 11, 2014 03:00AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 11 (Reuters) - Applications for U.S. home mortgages rose last week as both purchase and refinancing applications jumped, an industry group said on Wednesday.

The Mortgage Bankers Association said its seasonally adjusted index of mortgage application activity, which includes both refinancing and home purchase demand, rose 10.3 percent in the week ended June 6. The MBA's seasonally adjusted index of refinancing applications rose 11.0 percent, while the gauge of loan requests for home purchases, a leading indicator of home sales, increased 9.3 percent.  <^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ U.S. mortgage data: http://link.reuters.com/guv37s ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^> Fixed 30-year mortgage rates averaged 4.34 percent in the week, up 8 basis points from 4.26 percent the week before.